1
00:00:10,533 --> 00:00:12,533
<i>I'm the one Will asked to sub
for him during your operation.</i>

2
00:00:12,667 --> 00:00:13,567
<i> Corporal Allen Matibag.</i>

3
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:14,967
<i> I can't do it, I can't do it.</i>

4
00:00:15,100 --> 00:00:15,500
<i> Anika?</i>

5
00:00:15,633 --> 00:00:16,233
<i> There's Anika.</i>

6
00:00:16,367 --> 00:00:17,300
<i> Who's the guy with her?</i>

7
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:19,133
<i>Come with me if you don't want
to get hurt.</i>

8
00:00:19,267 --> 00:00:19,867
<i> Wait, Bro.</i>

9
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,233
<i> We can't catch up with them.</i>

10
00:00:21,367 --> 00:00:23,100
<i>- There! Take that one.
- Let's go.</i>

11
00:00:23,233 --> 00:00:24,433
<i> Hey, that's our bike! Hey!</i>

12
00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:26,633
<i>It depends on whether you
tell me who your supplier is.</i>

13
00:00:26,767 --> 00:00:27,633
<i> It's Jhem.</i>

14
00:00:27,767 --> 00:00:29,833
<i>Tell her to meet you
at Malindang Park.</i>

15
00:00:29,967 --> 00:00:33,967
<i>Enriquez, just leave the search
for Mando to them.</i>

16
00:00:34,133 --> 00:00:36,167
<i>Here are the pictures
of the four prisoners</i>

17
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:38,333
<i>who escaped from Calabari
Prison.</i>

18
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:40,133
<i> Operation Manhunt starts now.</i>

19
00:00:40,267 --> 00:00:41,600
<i> Just assign Mando to me.</i>

20
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:42,633
<i> I'll take care of him.</i>

21
00:00:42,767 --> 00:00:43,733
<i> Bro, this is their car.</i>

22
00:00:43,867 --> 00:00:44,433
<i> Yes, that's the one.</i>

23
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:45,567
<i> Guys, I need your help.</i>

24
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,500
<i>You need to get
to Malindang Park right now.</i>

25
00:00:47,633 --> 00:00:49,100
<i> Why did you choose Mando?</i>

26
00:00:49,233 --> 00:00:51,933
<i>We know that Sir Tonyo
is Mando's target, right?</i>

27
00:00:52,067 --> 00:00:53,100
<i>Right now, he can't do anything</i>

28
00:00:53,233 --> 00:00:54,567
<i>because he knows there are a lot
of police officers</i>

29
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:55,667
<i> at the hospital.</i>

30
00:00:55,800 --> 00:00:57,667
<i>But I won't wait for that, Sir.
I'll move now.</i>

31
00:00:57,800 --> 00:01:01,867
<i>The prisoners can't escape
just like that.</i>

32
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,200
<i>I think they have a proper
connection.</i>

33
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:07,067
<i> I think we have a new enemy.</i>

34
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:09,567
<i>Go hide. Your face
is all over the news.</i>

35
00:01:09,733 --> 00:01:11,233
<i> Boss, this is Mando.</i>

36
00:01:11,367 --> 00:01:12,567
<i> I will work on that.</i>

37
00:01:12,700 --> 00:01:14,000
<i> I just need to finish this.</i>

38
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:19,967
I don't know.

39
00:01:20,100 --> 00:01:22,400
It happened so fast.

40
00:01:22,533 --> 00:01:27,033
He pointed a gun at me,
and then I couldn't do anything.

41
00:01:27,167 --> 00:01:28,933
How much was stolen?

42
00:01:30,267 --> 00:01:32,000
It was about three
thousand pesos,

43
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:36,133
and the item he took costs
one thousand five hundred pesos.

44
00:01:36,267 --> 00:01:37,433
What item was that?

45
00:01:37,567 --> 00:01:39,600
It looks like this.

46
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:42,500
Teddy bear, one of the things
we sell.

47
00:01:42,667 --> 00:01:45,833
He took the pink teddy bear.

48
00:01:48,033 --> 00:01:50,600
Good thing it was caught
on CCTV.

49
00:01:53,533 --> 00:01:56,700
<i> Oh my!</i>

50
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:59,200
<i> Please don't!</i>

51
00:02:00,233 --> 00:02:01,833
I know him.

52
00:02:01,967 --> 00:02:04,167
That's Rodell Pacheco.

53
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:06,000
He has multiple theft cases.

54
00:02:06,133 --> 00:02:08,000
I remember him
from the news earlier.

55
00:02:08,133 --> 00:02:09,567
He's from Sta. Lucia,

56
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:11,867
boundary of Calabari
and our town.

57
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,233
It's just near here.

58
00:02:15,267 --> 00:02:17,400
Miss, stop crying.

59
00:02:17,533 --> 00:02:19,900
We'll make sure to catch
that thief.

60
00:02:20,033 --> 00:02:22,567
I'll hold on to that,
Sir, Ma'am.

61
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:24,800
Let's go.

62
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:13,233
Anika!

63
00:03:13,367 --> 00:03:14,467
Jhem.

64
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:15,567
What happened?

65
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:17,633
Have you and Vic talked yet?

66
00:03:17,767 --> 00:03:20,167
And why did we meet here?

67
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:22,133
Sorry, Jhem,
I don't have a choice.

68
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,167
I'm really sorry, Jhem.

69
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:25,733
I don't really have a choice.
I'm sorry.

70
00:03:25,867 --> 00:03:26,767
What are you saying?

71
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:36,400
Jhem...

72
00:03:36,533 --> 00:03:37,867
Anika, what is this?

73
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,667
I was the one who asked you
to come here.

74
00:03:40,867 --> 00:03:43,567
Don't worry,
Monty is my co-worker.

75
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:46,133
So he gave you
the remaining items?

76
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:48,433
What do you need?

77
00:03:49,533 --> 00:03:52,000
I just want to get
the remaining items.

78
00:03:53,267 --> 00:03:54,367
I'll take care of selling them,

79
00:03:54,533 --> 00:03:56,133
so you won't be bothered
anymore.

80
00:03:56,267 --> 00:03:58,167
Just tell me
where you kept them.

81
00:04:11,867 --> 00:04:13,600
Bro, there they are.

82
00:04:13,733 --> 00:04:15,667
Who's that other girl?

83
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,000
That's not important anymore,
Bro.

84
00:04:17,133 --> 00:04:18,100
Look, he's pointing a gun
at them.

85
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:19,867
Come on, we need to take action!

86
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,800
We have to wait
for the right time.

87
00:04:21,933 --> 00:04:22,767
Come on, let's go around.

88
00:04:22,900 --> 00:04:23,333
Come on, hurry!

89
00:04:23,467 --> 00:04:24,133
Come on.

90
00:04:35,233 --> 00:04:36,733
What do you want?

91
00:04:36,867 --> 00:04:38,900
I already told them everything.

92
00:04:39,033 --> 00:04:42,933
Romel, I'm Master Sergeant
Bobby Enriquez,

93
00:04:43,067 --> 00:04:46,667
and this is my partner,
Patrolman Jake Noble.

94
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:50,900
Maybe you remember something
Mando mentioned to you.

95
00:04:51,033 --> 00:04:53,800
Anything that might help us
find him.

96
00:04:55,433 --> 00:04:58,433
Nothing, you're just repeating
yourself.

97
00:04:58,567 --> 00:05:02,867
Our plan is, until we escape,
we'll be on our own after that.

98
00:05:03,033 --> 00:05:05,800
Do you know who helped you
escape?

99
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:08,433
It's possible that he helped
Mando hide.

100
00:05:08,567 --> 00:05:10,100
He didn't mention anything
either.

101
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:13,567
Just someone with a lot
of contacts and connections

102
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:14,933
here in Calabari.

103
00:05:19,067 --> 00:05:21,767
Do you know why he helped him
escape?

104
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:23,433
No.

105
00:05:23,567 --> 00:05:27,067
Mando said that he was
his old boss.

106
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:30,200
I don't know. Maybe he's got
a new job for him to do.

107
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:32,367
Okay, thank you.

108
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:34,567
Wait, wait.

109
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:38,033
Maybe you can talk to Warden.

110
00:05:39,133 --> 00:05:41,000
I'm having a hard time
being isolated here.

111
00:05:41,133 --> 00:05:42,367
I'm sorry.

112
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,933
That's the result
of your bad decision.

113
00:05:45,067 --> 00:05:47,167
We really hope that
you're telling the truth,

114
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:51,867
because if Mando hurts someone,
it's on your hands too.

115
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:54,567
Let's go.

116
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:10,667
That's too bad, Conde.

117
00:06:11,767 --> 00:06:13,700
Your girlfriend is already dead.

118
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:15,067
The problem is...

119
00:06:16,267 --> 00:06:20,067
who can I use to get you
out of the hospital?

120
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:24,233
<i> Hurry up, hurry up!</i>

121
00:06:29,633 --> 00:06:30,200
There you go.

122
00:06:30,333 --> 00:06:32,300
Hey, Selena, you're crazy.

123
00:06:32,433 --> 00:06:34,533
Does Sir Tonyo know
that you have a duplicate key

124
00:06:34,667 --> 00:06:35,933
to his house?

125
00:06:36,067 --> 00:06:38,600
Oh, come on. Of course,
I didn't tell him.

126
00:06:38,733 --> 00:06:40,000
Oh my, Sis.

127
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:42,300
You're crazy!
You're really assuming.

128
00:06:42,467 --> 00:06:44,367
Well, it's useful, isn't it?

129
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:46,433
I'm sure Sir Tonyo needs
a change of clothes

130
00:06:46,567 --> 00:06:47,400
at the hospital.

131
00:06:47,533 --> 00:06:49,600
It's better to have some
rather than none.

132
00:06:49,733 --> 00:06:50,567
- You do have a point.
- Come on.

133
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:51,567
- Come on, let's hurry.
- Hurry.

134
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:52,667
Sir Tonyo is waiting.

135
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:54,167
Hurry, hurry.

136
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:58,167
My contact said that Rodell
Pacheco's former residence

137
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,733
is in this village.

138
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:03,167
We need to catch him
as soon as possible.

139
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:05,333
He might hurt someone else.

140
00:07:12,067 --> 00:07:12,800
Positive.

141
00:07:12,933 --> 00:07:13,633
There he is.

142
00:07:28,733 --> 00:07:29,367
Son of a...

143
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:30,467
- Let's go!
- Hurry!

144
00:07:35,233 --> 00:07:36,100
Stop!

145
00:07:36,233 --> 00:07:37,167
- Let's go!
- Get out of the way!

146
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:39,667
- Hey! Come here!
- Get out of the way!

147
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:41,733
Hey! Let's go this way!

148
00:07:41,867 --> 00:07:42,900
Hey!

149
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:48,667
Hey! Hey, stop!

150
00:07:49,933 --> 00:07:50,500
Hey!

151
00:07:50,633 --> 00:07:51,333
Come on, let's go.

152
00:07:54,733 --> 00:07:56,633
I want to talk to Monty first.

153
00:07:56,767 --> 00:07:57,833
What's the point?

154
00:07:57,967 --> 00:07:59,133
Are you guys dating?

155
00:07:59,267 --> 00:08:00,967
You're still young!

156
00:08:01,100 --> 00:08:03,233
I need to talk to Monty.

157
00:08:03,367 --> 00:08:05,900
I need to know if he knows
what you're doing.

158
00:08:06,033 --> 00:08:08,433
You don't seem to understand,
Kid.

159
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:12,900
Monty works for me,
so you need to listen to me!

160
00:08:13,033 --> 00:08:15,267
You won't know
where the remaining items are.

161
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:18,933
Unless you tell me that you can
get Monty out of jail.

162
00:08:27,433 --> 00:08:27,967
Hey!

163
00:08:28,100 --> 00:08:29,700
Come here. Kneel!

164
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:31,033
Don't fight back. Kneel!

165
00:08:32,233 --> 00:08:33,367
Don't fight back.

166
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:34,867
Rodell Pacheco,
you're caught already.

167
00:08:37,867 --> 00:08:39,200
Rodell?

168
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:40,200
Rodell...

169
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,867
Dad's there?

170
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:45,567
Dad!

171
00:08:47,033 --> 00:08:49,467
I'm glad you came
to my birthday.

172
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:53,033
Are they the ones you said were
your hide-and-seek friends?

173
00:08:53,167 --> 00:08:54,733
Yes, my child.

174
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:56,933
But they caught me.

175
00:08:57,067 --> 00:08:59,000
Are you happy that I'm here
on your birthday?

176
00:08:59,133 --> 00:09:00,700
Your dress looks nice,
my child.

177
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:04,767
My child, this is my gift
to you.

178
00:09:09,733 --> 00:09:10,600
Wow!

179
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:12,567
This is beautiful!

180
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:14,733
Thank you, Dad!

181
00:09:14,867 --> 00:09:16,667
I know you've wanted this
for a long time.

182
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:19,867
Happy birthday, my child.

183
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,533
Your dad loves you very much.

184
00:09:34,033 --> 00:09:35,467
Peach...

185
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:36,700
Sir Tonyo will be happy.

186
00:09:36,833 --> 00:09:38,133
He has a complete set
of clothes.

187
00:09:38,267 --> 00:09:40,233
You know, girl,
you're so obvious.

188
00:09:40,367 --> 00:09:41,300
What do you mean?

189
00:09:41,433 --> 00:09:42,867
That you like Sir Tonyo.

190
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,400
You know, we used to be
like that too.

191
00:09:44,533 --> 00:09:47,967
But we've long accepted
that Tonyo loves someone else.

192
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:49,233
Who?

193
00:09:49,367 --> 00:09:53,933
The beautiful police officer
he works with, Ma'am Bobby.

194
00:09:55,367 --> 00:09:56,633
During the fiesta,

195
00:09:56,767 --> 00:09:58,467
there was something in the way
they looked at each other.

196
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,200
You know, that's just
your hunch.

197
00:10:01,367 --> 00:10:04,467
As for me, I feel
that Sir Tonyo likes me.

198
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:06,200
Okay? Let's go.

199
00:10:06,333 --> 00:10:07,400
Come on.

200
00:10:13,567 --> 00:10:16,133
Where can I find Bobby?

201
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:23,633
It means you did all this
to give your daughter

202
00:10:23,767 --> 00:10:25,067
a present for her birthday?

203
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,667
And to give money to my wife.

204
00:10:28,967 --> 00:10:31,133
I haven't given her money
in a long time.

205
00:10:37,900 --> 00:10:38,733
Love...

206
00:10:39,933 --> 00:10:40,933
what now?

207
00:10:41,067 --> 00:10:43,567
Everything you gave us
was stolen.

208
00:10:43,700 --> 00:10:46,100
We need to return this money

209
00:10:46,233 --> 00:10:48,400
and your daughter's teddy bear
as well.

210
00:10:48,533 --> 00:10:52,400
I'll take care of that, Ma'am,
and the vendor whom he robbed.

211
00:10:52,533 --> 00:10:53,967
Thank you.

212
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:54,800
Really, Boss?

213
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:57,267
Thank you very much.

214
00:10:57,400 --> 00:10:58,733
Don't thank me.

215
00:11:00,267 --> 00:11:01,633
I just remembered my father.

216
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:03,767
He's like that to me, too.

217
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:05,500
He's always absent
on my birthdays.

218
00:11:05,633 --> 00:11:09,300
But I'm sorry, we need
to take you back to Calabari.

219
00:11:12,167 --> 00:11:13,500
I understand.

220
00:11:13,633 --> 00:11:16,167
I know I won't last long
as a fugitive.

221
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:19,300
I just want to see my family
on my daughter's birthday.

222
00:11:22,967 --> 00:11:23,667
Let's go.

223
00:11:25,567 --> 00:11:26,667
Rodell...

224
00:11:28,567 --> 00:11:29,400
Dad!

225
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:33,400
Are you leaving again?

226
00:11:33,533 --> 00:11:34,933
Yes, my child.

227
00:11:35,067 --> 00:11:36,633
When are you coming back?

228
00:11:38,533 --> 00:11:39,733
I don't know yet.

229
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,867
Thank you for the teddy bear,
Dad.

230
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:47,600
I love you, Dad!

231
00:12:15,500 --> 00:12:16,433
Jhem...

232
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:18,567
Jhem, tell him where
the pimple patches are.

233
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:20,233
Tell him, please.

234
00:12:20,367 --> 00:12:21,667
- Please.
- No.

235
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:23,600
I'm not afraid of him, Anika.

236
00:12:23,733 --> 00:12:25,333
He needs something from me.

237
00:12:28,400 --> 00:12:30,067
I know you can't kill me.

238
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:33,400
Unless I tell you where the
remaining items are, right?

239
00:12:33,533 --> 00:12:35,767
So if I were you,
stop wasting your time

240
00:12:35,900 --> 00:12:38,733
and tell me that you're going
to get Monty out of jail!

241
00:12:38,867 --> 00:12:40,333
When he gets out, fine,

242
00:12:40,467 --> 00:12:42,833
I'll give you those damn
pimple patches!

243
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:54,133
You know, you're right.

244
00:12:54,267 --> 00:12:55,833
I can't kill you...

245
00:12:57,033 --> 00:12:58,233
but I can kill her.

246
00:13:00,033 --> 00:13:01,033
Anika!

247
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:03,300
Anika!

248
00:13:03,433 --> 00:13:04,233
Shut up!

249
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:05,900
You animal!

250
00:13:06,033 --> 00:13:07,067
Do you want to be the next one?

251
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,700
Where are the remaining items?

252
00:13:10,633 --> 00:13:11,367
Where?

253
00:13:24,833 --> 00:13:25,800
Don't move!

254
00:13:29,833 --> 00:13:30,600
Hey, stop!

255
00:13:30,733 --> 00:13:31,633
Vince, wait a minute!

256
00:13:34,367 --> 00:13:36,867
I know we're tired,
sleep-deprived, and hungry.

257
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,800
Don't worry.

258
00:13:38,933 --> 00:13:41,167
I'll have the food delivered,
okay?

259
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:43,600
- Sir, thank you!
- Sure!

260
00:13:45,467 --> 00:13:46,567
Samson, Paloma.

261
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:47,667
Chief.

262
00:13:48,767 --> 00:13:50,733
What are you doing here?
What's up?

263
00:13:50,867 --> 00:13:53,467
One of the fugitives
were found near our area.

264
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:55,900
We caught him.
He's in jail already.

265
00:13:56,067 --> 00:13:56,733
Really?

266
00:13:58,067 --> 00:13:58,933
Thank you very much!

267
00:13:59,067 --> 00:13:59,833
You're welcome.

268
00:13:59,967 --> 00:14:01,533
Thank you very much
for your help.

269
00:14:01,667 --> 00:14:04,167
Perfect timing.
Don't leave just yet, okay?

270
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:05,400
I ordered some food.

271
00:14:05,533 --> 00:14:07,033
Let's eat here.

272
00:14:07,167 --> 00:14:08,967
- Yes, okay.
- Okay.

273
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:10,500
Come in.

274
00:14:10,633 --> 00:14:11,467
Let's go.

275
00:14:14,567 --> 00:14:15,233
Enriquez!

276
00:14:15,367 --> 00:14:15,800
Sir.

277
00:14:15,933 --> 00:14:16,867
What's the update?

278
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:19,833
Sir, we came from Mando's
old house.

279
00:14:19,967 --> 00:14:21,833
It's now a factory.

280
00:14:21,967 --> 00:14:25,333
Bobby, we've caught
one of the fugitives.

281
00:14:25,467 --> 00:14:26,833
He's in jail already.

282
00:14:26,967 --> 00:14:27,800
Thank you.

283
00:14:28,933 --> 00:14:29,700
Bobby.

284
00:14:31,767 --> 00:14:32,633
Major.

285
00:14:32,767 --> 00:14:35,233
Major, a tip came in
about Mandong Warak.

286
00:14:35,367 --> 00:14:36,467
Did you check if it's legit?

287
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:37,600
Yes, Sir.

288
00:14:37,733 --> 00:14:40,000
The caller sent a picture,
but it's a bit blurry.

289
00:14:40,133 --> 00:14:40,967
Let me take a look.

290
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:43,700
Enriquez...

291
00:14:44,867 --> 00:14:46,000
go there.

292
00:14:46,133 --> 00:14:49,067
Bobby, do you need backup?

293
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:51,233
Thank you very much,
Lieutenant Samson,

294
00:14:51,367 --> 00:14:52,667
but we can handle it.

295
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,200
- Sir, we'll go ahead.
- Okay, be careful.

296
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:01,833
I'm really good
at faking things.

297
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:04,700
Let's see if they will take
this bait.

298
00:15:07,967 --> 00:15:09,900
Go ahead.

299
00:15:10,033 --> 00:15:11,500
Send someone over.

300
00:15:13,233 --> 00:15:16,233
I miss killing a cop too.

301
00:15:22,567 --> 00:15:23,167
Hey, stop!

302
00:15:38,467 --> 00:15:39,800
I'll kill you!

303
00:15:46,867 --> 00:15:49,067
Don't kill me, please.

304
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:50,967
Miss, don't be afraid.
I'm a police officer.

305
00:15:55,467 --> 00:15:59,333
Are you going to arrest me?
I'm not a bad person.

306
00:15:59,467 --> 00:16:02,567
I just really want Monty
to get out of jail.

307
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:04,367
Please, don't...

308
00:16:04,700 --> 00:16:06,567
Miss, we already know that
you're Monty's girlfriend.

309
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:08,533
But I'm sorry,
I have to arrest you

310
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:11,233
because you're selling
pimple patch drugs on campus.

311
00:16:11,367 --> 00:16:14,667
If I were you, Miss,
I'd confess and surrender.

312
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:15,600
Tell everything.

313
00:16:15,733 --> 00:16:17,267
Maybe your sentence
will be reduced.

314
00:16:19,267 --> 00:16:19,967
Hey!

315
00:16:21,633 --> 00:16:23,267
What are you doing
to our friend?

316
00:16:38,033 --> 00:16:39,167
Hey!

317
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:40,567
Hey, come back here!

318
00:16:43,167 --> 00:16:45,300
Who were you talking to earlier?

319
00:16:45,433 --> 00:16:49,833
I don't really know him,
but he's Monty's boss.

320
00:16:51,433 --> 00:16:52,467
Where's the stash?

321
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:54,433
The pimple patch drugs
you were selling on campus?

322
00:16:56,867 --> 00:16:58,400
It's in my dorm.

323
00:17:00,933 --> 00:17:03,000
Anika!

324
00:17:07,133 --> 00:17:08,467
What's our plan, Ma'am?

325
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:13,533
Chief said we need a positive
identification of Mando.

326
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:18,700
Once we see him,
we'll call for backup.

327
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:20,267
Copy.

328
00:17:20,400 --> 00:17:21,167
Noble...

329
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,800
Remember...

330
00:17:23,933 --> 00:17:25,833
no one's going to engage.

331
00:17:25,967 --> 00:17:29,433
Let's just ID him,
then we'll regroup here.

332
00:17:29,567 --> 00:17:30,333
It's clear, Ma'am.

333
00:17:30,467 --> 00:17:32,600
Okay. Go there, I'll check here.

334
00:18:01,867 --> 00:18:02,867
Bobby...

335
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:10,767
Sir Tonyo!

336
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:14,500
- Good thing you're awake!
- Hi, Sir Tonyo.

337
00:18:16,067 --> 00:18:17,033
No need for that.

338
00:18:17,167 --> 00:18:18,467
You're just interrupting
our moment here.

339
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:22,100
Sir Tonyo, here. We brought you
your clothes.

340
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,033
My clothes?

341
00:18:25,167 --> 00:18:29,000
Sir Tonyo, don't ask where
your clothes came from.

342
00:18:29,133 --> 00:18:32,000
She's right. Or where did
we get your clothes.

343
00:18:32,133 --> 00:18:35,133
We're not involved in that.
That's all Selena's doing.

344
00:18:35,267 --> 00:18:38,500
Okay, fine. I'll take
all the credit.

345
00:18:38,633 --> 00:18:41,700
Come on, girls. Sir Tonyo
hasn't fully recovered yet.

346
00:18:41,833 --> 00:18:43,500
But it's true, Sir Tonyo.

347
00:18:43,633 --> 00:18:46,000
I'm the one who chose
your t-shirt, your shorts,

348
00:18:46,133 --> 00:18:48,233
even your briefs!

349
00:18:48,367 --> 00:18:50,100
You know, do you want anything?

350
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:52,033
Do you want to eat?
Are you thirsty?

351
00:18:52,167 --> 00:18:55,500
The doctor said that
we can change your clothes.

352
00:18:55,667 --> 00:18:57,367
I'll just change your clothes.

353
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:58,767
Do you want me to give you
a bath too?

354
00:18:58,900 --> 00:19:00,300
I know how to give
a sponge bath.

355
00:19:00,433 --> 00:19:02,667
We have fruits here as well.

356
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:04,267
We brought you some fruits.

357
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:36,433
Solid job.

358
00:19:36,567 --> 00:19:38,633
Conde made the right choice
when he chose the two of you.

359
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:42,867
And I also heard about
you covering for Mariano.

360
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:44,567
Thank you very much, Matibag.

361
00:19:44,700 --> 00:19:46,033
It's part of the job, Chief.

362
00:19:46,167 --> 00:19:49,367
Good thing, Sir, my friends
have arrived.

363
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:51,433
Otherwise, I'd be dead by now.

364
00:19:51,567 --> 00:19:54,133
Yes, Sir. Sir, maybe we can get
something to eat there.

365
00:19:54,267 --> 00:19:55,800
- We're hungry.
- Hey!

366
00:19:55,933 --> 00:19:58,233
You always expect something
in return for everything you do.

367
00:19:58,367 --> 00:19:59,833
- Sir, I'm sorry.
- Why? Is it bad to be hungry?

368
00:19:59,967 --> 00:20:01,933
Abi is downstairs
and brought some food.

369
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:02,867
Get whatever you want.

370
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:03,933
That's what I'm talking about!

371
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:06,900
- There you go!
- Thank you, Sir.

372
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:08,167
Eat well!

373
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:09,767
Nice!

374
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:11,067
Sir...

375
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:12,433
what now?

376
00:20:12,567 --> 00:20:14,400
We didn't catch the guy Jhem
was talking to last night.

377
00:20:14,533 --> 00:20:17,800
Well, you said you could
describe him to our artist,

378
00:20:17,933 --> 00:20:18,433
right?

379
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:21,467
And he also left his gun behind,
right?

380
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:22,467
Yes, Sir.

381
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:24,633
We'll profile him.

382
00:20:24,767 --> 00:20:25,933
It'll be easier to find him.

383
00:20:26,067 --> 00:20:27,633
Sir, by the way...

384
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:30,500
as for Jhem, what's going
to happen to her?

385
00:20:30,633 --> 00:20:32,900
She'll definitely go to jail

386
00:20:33,033 --> 00:20:35,733
for selling the pimple patch
drugs.

387
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:39,433
And we also got a large volume
of drugs in her dorm.

388
00:20:40,767 --> 00:20:45,000
- She's beautiful, what a shame!
- She's too young, what a shame!

389
00:20:45,133 --> 00:20:46,333
What did she do?

390
00:20:46,467 --> 00:20:49,600
You wasted your life.

391
00:20:49,733 --> 00:20:52,533
I think she's the same age
as my child.

392
00:20:52,667 --> 00:20:54,367
You're so beautiful, Miss.

393
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:58,333
Sit down, Miss.

394
00:20:58,467 --> 00:21:00,533
You're so beautiful,
what a shame.

395
00:21:00,667 --> 00:21:02,100
What did she do?

396
00:21:02,233 --> 00:21:03,667
Sorry, Monty.

397
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:32,200
You're useless!

398
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:34,367
I'm paying you, right?

399
00:21:34,500 --> 00:21:36,233
Wait, Boss, relax, easy.

400
00:21:36,367 --> 00:21:37,333
Why am I involved in this?

401
00:21:37,467 --> 00:21:39,067
You asked me to lie low,
remember?

402
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,633
Go ahead and ask yourself.

403
00:21:40,767 --> 00:21:42,633
Why were you asked to lie low?

404
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:43,967
Because you're a failure!

405
00:21:45,067 --> 00:21:46,500
You're a failure, Roman!

406
00:21:48,367 --> 00:21:49,667
And you, Dante...

407
00:21:50,967 --> 00:21:54,000
two women,
and you can't handle them?

408
00:21:54,133 --> 00:21:55,533
You can't handle them?

409
00:21:55,667 --> 00:21:59,100
Boss, I told you some guys
interfered,

410
00:21:59,233 --> 00:22:00,933
that's why my plan was ruined.

411
00:22:01,067 --> 00:22:05,433
I almost got Monty's girlfriend
to confess where our items were.

412
00:22:05,567 --> 00:22:06,567
Almost?

413
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,033
Where are they now?

414
00:22:08,167 --> 00:22:10,200
Aren't they in the hands
of the police?

415
00:22:10,333 --> 00:22:12,833
Even my products,
they've been thrown away!

416
00:22:12,967 --> 00:22:14,567
They probably even
recognized you!

417
00:22:14,700 --> 00:22:15,967
And aside from that...

418
00:22:16,133 --> 00:22:18,400
Aside from that,
you left your gun behind.

419
00:22:18,533 --> 00:22:19,967
You're so stupid!

420
00:22:21,267 --> 00:22:24,600
Boss, you know that they don't
have a record of me.

421
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:26,767
So they can't get anything out
of me.

422
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:28,633
And you've really got the nerve
to talk back?

423
00:22:28,767 --> 00:22:29,900
Really?

424
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:36,467
It's only a matter of time
before that Monty talks.

425
00:22:40,933 --> 00:22:47,300
You know, you two, I don't care
what you have to do.

426
00:22:47,433 --> 00:22:52,600
Monty and his girlfriend
must be killed.

427
00:22:52,767 --> 00:22:54,267
Do you understand that?

428
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:57,900
Do you understand that?

429
00:22:58,033 --> 00:22:59,100
Yes, Boss.

430
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:02,067
Go ahead and leave!

431
00:23:16,867 --> 00:23:17,833
<i> What now?</i>

432
00:23:17,967 --> 00:23:19,500
This won't take long, Boss.

433
00:23:19,633 --> 00:23:21,800
My project is almost finished.

434
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:25,000
After this, I'm all yours.

435
00:23:25,133 --> 00:23:27,200
Let's make things clear, Mando.

436
00:23:27,333 --> 00:23:29,333
I gave you the money,

437
00:23:29,467 --> 00:23:31,467
so I wouldn't have
to worry about you.

438
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:34,733
Boss, this won't take long.

439
00:23:34,867 --> 00:23:38,467
You know that Conde ruined
my life, right?

440
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:39,967
I'm just going to get even.

441
00:23:40,100 --> 00:23:44,267
I've found a way
to go after Conde.

442
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:47,633
I have his love team now,

443
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:52,733
Master Sergeant
Roberta Enriquez.

444
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:56,233
Bobby?

445
00:24:01,633 --> 00:24:02,467
Yes, Boss.

446
00:24:03,933 --> 00:24:05,267
Do you know her, too?

447
00:24:08,033 --> 00:24:10,267
We won't have any problems,
Boss?

448
00:24:11,667 --> 00:24:12,867
None.

449
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:16,333
Report to me afterwards.

450
00:24:16,467 --> 00:24:17,267
Great.

451
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,233
Hello, Noble?

452
00:24:38,367 --> 00:24:39,400
Did Ma'am Enriquez contact you?

453
00:24:39,533 --> 00:24:40,700
No, why?

454
00:24:40,833 --> 00:24:42,767
She suddenly disappeared from
the place you asked us to check.

455
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:43,500
What?

456
00:24:43,633 --> 00:24:44,500
Let me go.

457
00:24:44,633 --> 00:24:45,600
Hey!

458
00:24:46,667 --> 00:24:48,767
I'll send our picture
to your boyfriend, okay?

459
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:51,233
It's Enriquez,
Mandong Warak got her.

460
00:24:51,367 --> 00:24:52,900
Sir Tonyo is really
something else, Sir.

461
00:24:53,033 --> 00:24:55,300
He really went alone
to save Ma'am Bobby.

462
00:24:55,433 --> 00:24:57,767
If I were in his situation,
I would do the same.

463
00:24:57,900 --> 00:24:59,300
Do you have a special
someone too, Sir?

464
00:24:59,433 --> 00:25:00,533
Special someone?

465
00:25:00,667 --> 00:25:02,200
Leave Bobby alone.

466
00:25:02,367 --> 00:25:05,600
Not yet. I still want to play
with you.
